{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Voxel occupancy prediction uses the cross-entropy-based occupancy loss L occ, applied to the predictions generated by an MLP on P fin.",
    "The Image-to-Query Detector utilizes the detection loss L det from Sparse4D v3 [28].",
    "To improve voxel representation, we incorporate an Auxiliary Mask Decoder with the mask loss L mask, as described in Mask2Former [5].In addition, the forecasting head refines the warped historical voxel features by predicting the corrected current occupancy distribution, which is supervised using a crossentropy loss L fore.",
    "The occupied mask head determines whether each voxel is filled or empty and is supervised with a binary cross-entropy loss L bin.",
    "The total loss function L total is defined as:L total = λ depth • L depth + λ occ • L occ + λ det • L det + λ mask • L mask + λ fore • L fore + λ bin • L bin,(11)where λ depth, λ occ, λ det, λ mask, λ fore, and λ bin are the balancing weights for each loss term."
  ],
